obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (46646)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46646&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the ^1Pensions Act, 1871.`
  line
  line `Extent of Act.-- ^2[In so far as it relates to Union pensions, it extends to the whole of India and in so far as it relates to other pensions, it extends] to ^3[the whole of India except ^4[the territories which, immediately before the 1st November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States]].`
  line
  line `^5* * * * *`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `In section 1, for the entry under the heading “Extent of Act”, the following entry shall be substituted,`
  line `namely:-`
  line
  line `“It extends to the whole of the State of Karnataka.”`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 23 of 1979, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. It has been amended in its application to U. P. by U. P. Act 12 of 1922. Rep. in part in West Bengal by West Bengal, Act 7 of`
  line 1948.
  line
  line `The Act has been extended to and brought into force in Dadra and Nagar Haveli by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and the First`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 1-7-1965) and extended to the whole of the Union Territory of Lakshadweep by Reg. 8 of 1965, s. 3 and the`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 1-10-1967).`
  line
  line `The Act has been repealed in its application to Bellary District by Mysore Act 14 of 1955.`
  line
  line `2. Subs, by Act 20 of 1982, s. 2, for "It extend".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O.1950, for "all the Provinces of India" which had been subs. by the A.O.1948, for "the whole of British`
  line `India".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for "Part B States".`
  line
  line `5. The words "And it shall come into force on the date of the passing thereof" rep, by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second`
  line Schedule.
  line
  line `6. The words "but not so as to affect any suit in respect of a pension or grant of money or land-revenue which may have been`
  line `instituted before such date rep. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (46630)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46630&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `[Enactments repealed. Saving of Rules. Rep. by the Repealing Act, 1938 (1 of 1938),`
  line `s. 2 and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (46631)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Interpretation-Section.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46631&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, the expression grant of money or land-revenue`
  line `includes anything payable on the part of Government in respect of any right, privilege,`
  line `perquisite or office.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (46632)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46632&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Definition.--The expression the appropriate Government means, in relation to`
  line ^2
  line `Union pensions, the Central Government, and in relation to other pensions, the State`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by the A.O. 1937.`
  line `2. Sub. by the A.O. 1950, for federal.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (46648)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Bar of suits relating to pensions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, as amended by C.O. 29, for British or.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46648&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Except as hereinafter provided no Civil Court shall`
  line `entertain any suit relating to any pension or grant of money or land-revenue conferred or made`
  line `by the ^1[Government or by] any former Government, whatever may have been the consideration`
  line `for any such pension or grant, and whatever may have been the nature of the payment, claim or`
  line `right for which such pension or grant may have been substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (46634)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Claims to be made to collector, Deputy Commissioner or other authorised officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46634&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Any person having a claim`
  line `relating to any such pension or grant may prefer such claim to the Collector of the District or`
  line `Deputy Commissioner or other officer authorized in this behalf by the ^1 [appropriate Government], and such Collector, Deputy Commissioner or other officer shall dispose of such`
  line `claim in accordance with such rules as the Chief Revenue authority may, subject to the general control of`
  line `the ^2[appropriate Government], from time to time prescribe in this behalf.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 5.--In section 5, of the words, "Any person having a claim", the words "Save`
  line `as otherwise provided in any law or any rule regulating payment of pension to persons appointed to public`
  line `services and posts in connection with the affairs of the State, any person having a claim" shall be`
  line `substituted and for the words as the Chief Revenue Authority may, subject to the general control of the`
  line `appropriate Government", the words "as the appropriate Government may" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 23 of 1979, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L. G.".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L. G.".`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (46635)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Civil Court empowered to take cognizance of such claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46635&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `A Civil Court, otherwise`
  line `competent to try the same, shall take cognizance of any such claim upon receiving a certificate from such`
  line `Collector, Deputy Commissioner or other officer authorized in that behalf that the case may be so tried,`
  line `but shall not make any order or decree in any suit whatever by which the liability of Government to pay`
  line `any such pension or grant as aforesaid is affected directly or indirectly.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (46636)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Pensions for lands held under grants in perpetuity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46636&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in sections 4 and 6 applies to--`
  line
  line `(1) any inam of the class referred to in section 1 of Madras Act No. IV of 1862^1`
  line ;
  line
  line `(2) pensions heretofore granted by Government in the territories respectively subject to the`
  line `Lieutenant-Governors of Bengal and the North-Western Provinces, either wholly or in part as an`
  line `indemnity for loss sustained by the resumption by a Native Government of lands held under sanads`
  line `purporting to confer a right in perpetuity. Such pensions shall not be liable to resumption on the death`
  line `of the recipient, but every such pension shall be capable of alienation and descent, and may be sued`
  line `for and recovered in the same manner as any other property.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. I.e., "inams of the classes described in el. 1, s. 2, [Mad]. Regulation 4 of 1831, which have been, or shall be, enfranchised by`
  line `the Inam Commissioner and converted into freeholds in perpetuity, or into absolute freeholds in perpetuity". The classes so`
  line `described are hereditary or personal grants of money or of land-revenue, however, denominated, conferred by the authority of`
  line `the Governor in Council or which, having been made by any Native Govt. have been confirmed or continued by the British`
  line `Govt.--Act 31 of 1836] in consideration of services rendered to the State or in lieu of resumed offices or privileges, or of`
  line `zamindaris or paleiyams forfeited or held under attachment or management by the officers of Govt., or as a yaumia or`
  line `charitable allowance, or as a pension".`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (46647)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Payment to be made by Deputy Commissioner, Collector or other authorised officer`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46647&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `All pensions or grants by`
  line `Government of money or land-revenue shall be paid by the Collector or the Deputy Commissioner or`
  line `other authorized officer, subject to such rules as may, from time to time, be prescribed by the Chief`
  line `Controlling Revenue-authority.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 8.--In section 8, for the words “All pensions or grants” the words “Save as`
  line `otherwise provided in any law or any rule regulating grant and payment of pension to persons appointed`
  line `to public services and posts in connection with the affairs of the State, all pensions or grants, shall be`
  line `substituted and for the words “Chief Controlling Revenue Authority” the words “appropriate`
  line `government” shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 23 of 1979, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (46638)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Saving of rights of grantees of land-revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46638&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in sections 4 and 8 shall affect the right`
  line `of a grantee of land-revenue, whose claim to such grant is admitted by Government, to recover such`
  line `revenue from the persons liable to pay the same under any law for the time being in force for the recovery`
  line `of the rent of land.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (46639)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Commutation of pensions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L. G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46639&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[appropriate Government] may, with the consent of the`
  line `holder, order the whole or any part of his pension or grant of money et land-revenue to be commuted for a`
  line `lump sum on such terms as may seem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (46649)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Exemption of pension from attachment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46649&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^111. Exemption of pension from attachment.--No pension granted or continued by Government`
  line `on political considerations, or on account of past services or present infirmities or as a`
  line `compassionate allowance,`
  line
  line `and no money due or to become due on account of any such pension or allowance,`
  line
  line `shall be liable to seizure, attachment or sequestration by process of any Court ^2*** at the instance of a`
  line `creditor, for any demand against the pensioner, or in satisfaction of a decree or order of any such Court.`
  line
  line `^3This section applies ^2*** also to pensions granted or continued^4`
  line `, after the separation of Burma fromIndia, by the Government of Burma.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. See also s. 60, clause (g) of the Code of Civil Procedure 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `2. The words "in Part A States and Part C States" omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956. The words "Part A`
  line `States and Part C States" were subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "the Provinces" which had been subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "British`
  line `India".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by the A. O. 1937.`
  line
  line `4. I.e., on or after the 1st April, 1937.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (46641)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Assignments, etc., in anticipation of pension, to be void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46641&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `All assignments, agreements'`
  line `orders, sales, and securities of every kind made by the person entitled to any pension, Pay or allowance`
  line `mentioned in section 11, in respect of any money not payable at or before the making thereof, on account`
  line `of any such pension, pay or allowance, or for giving or assigning any future interest therein, are null and`
  line void.
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (46642)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 14
  title `Nomination by pensioner to receive moneys outstanding on account of pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1982, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46642&sectionno=12A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Nomination by pensioner to receive moneys outstanding on account of pension.--Notwithstanding anything contained in section 12 or in any other law for the time being in force,--`
  line
  line `(a) any person to whom any pension mentioned in section 11 is payable by the Government of`
  line `India or out of the Consolidated Fund of India (such person being hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `pensioner) may nominate any other person (hereinafter referred to as the nominee), in such manner`
  line `and in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government by rules, to receive after the death`
  line `of the pensioner, all moneys payable to the pensioner on account of such pension at, before or after`
  line `the date of such nomination and which remain unpaid immediately before the death of the pensioner;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the nominee shall be entitled, on the death of the pensioner, to receive, to the exclusion of all`
  line `other persons, all such moneys which have so remained unpaid:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the nominee predeceases the pensioner, the nomination shall, so far as it relates to the`
  line `right conferred upon the said nominee, become void and of no effect:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where provision has been duly made in the nomination, in accordance with the`
  line `rules made by the Central Government, conferring upon some other person the right to receive all such`
  line `moneys, which have so remained unpaid, in the event of the nominee predeceasing the pensioner, such`
  line `right shall, upon the decease as aforesaid of the nominee, pass to such other person.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (46643)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Reward to informers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46643&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Whoever proves to the satisfaction of the ^1[appropriate Government]`
  line `that any pension is fraudulently or unduly received by the person enjoying the benefit thereof shall be`
  line `entitled to a reward equivalent to the amount of such pension for the period of six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (46644)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46644&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^2[In each State] the Chief Controlling Revenue Authority may, with the`
  line `consent of the ^1[appropriate Government], from time to time make rules consistent with this Act`
  line `respecting all or any of the following matters :--`
  line
  line `(1) the place and times at which, and the person to whom, any pension shall be paid;`
  line
  line `(2) inquiries into the identity of claimants;`
  line
  line `(3) records to be kept on the subject of pensions;`
  line
  line `(4) transmission of such records;`
  line
  line `(5) correction of such records;`
  line
  line `(6) delivery of certificates to pensioners;`
  line
  line `(7) registers of such certificates;`
  line
  line `(8) reference to the Civil Court, under section 6, of persons claiming a right of succession to, or`
  line `participation in, pensions or grants of money or land-revenue payable by Government;`
  line
  line `and generally for the guidance of officers under this Act.`
  line
  line `All such rules shall be published in the Official Gazette, and shall thereupon have the force of law.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 14.--In section 14, for the words, “Chief Controlling Revenue Authority may`
  line `with the consent of the appropriate Government”, the words “appropriate Government may” shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 23 of 1979, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G".`
  line
  line `2. Ins., ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (46650)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1982, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46650&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[15. Power of Central Government to make rules.--The Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, make rules to provide for all or any of the following matters, namely : --`
  line
  line `(a) the manner and form in which any nomination may be made under section 12A and the`
  line `manner and form in which such nomination may be cancelled or varied by another nomination;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which provision may be made, for the purposes of the second proviso to`
  line `section 12A, in any such nomination for conferring on some person other than the nominee the right`
  line `to receive moneys payable to the nominee if such nominee predeceases the pensioner.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (46645)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Laying of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 1982, s. 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051&sectionId=46645&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_89_00001_187123_1523268761051
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `^1[16. Laying of rules.--Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act and every rule`
  line `made under section 14 by a Chief Controlling Revenue Authority with the consent of the Central`
  line `Government, shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is`
  line `in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses`
  line `agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or`
  line `be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
